{"id":14880904,"mediaExerciseId":"8a3bf126-4ad2-409f-acd2-51bbf608dc23","exerciseName":"6","chapterName":"5","chapterTitle":"Introduction to Valuation:The Time Value of Money","groupId":612293,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":147,"solutions":[{"id":6063736,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we need to calculate at what rate we need to invest our money in order to meet a certain goal. This goal is to cover our child's college education in 18 years' time. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"We know the following values:\n\n\n| | | \n|--|--| \n|Initial Investment |$73,000 | \n|Years to Invest | 18 | \n| Goal| $345,000| \n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"For this, we are going to use the Present Value (PV) formula to find the needed rate of return to meet our goal. For that, we need to rearrange the formula.\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\nPV & = \\frac{FV}{(1+r)^t}\\\\\n\\\\\nr & =\\sqrt[t]{\\frac{FV}{PV}}-1\n\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n*Where:*\n- FV is the future value\n- t are the times the rate is applied\n- r is the applied rate","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"Now we use the data that we have to calculate the rate.\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\nr & =\\sqrt[18]{\\frac{\\$345,000}{\\$73,000}}-1\\\\\n\\\\\n& =\\boxed{9.01\\%}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe needed annual return rate to meet our goal is **9.01%**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"9.01%","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":true,"stepNumber":5}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"059788f8-a771-4338-a2ce-720830ad7a18","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":5}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880905,"exerciseName":"7","page":147,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"559fcd9a-edbb-4b8b-be35-dc07b0ea1b78","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-5-questions-and-problems-7-559fcd9a-edbb-4b8b-be35-dc07b0ea1b78"},{"id":14880906,"exerciseName":"8","page":147,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"11ebe094-4c6d-4745-8043-0cb7356b7927","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-5-questions-and-problems-8-11ebe094-4c6d-4745-8043-0cb7356b7927"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14880903,"exerciseName":"5","page":147,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"49fb1ee8-9b41-446f-8eaa-101ebd8a4a70","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-5-questions-and-problems-5-49fb1ee8-9b41-446f-8eaa-101ebd8a4a70"},{"id":14880902,"exerciseName":"4","page":147,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"6691c9bb-189b-47bf-b244-a147335b1e4c","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-so